<b>Subject:</b> Re: My Two Cents<p>
<br><center><img src="http://www.everworld.net/pvpquest/images/divider.gif" width=452 height=22 border=0></center><BR><P ALIGN=CENTER><b>In Reply To:</b> <A HREF="http://www.everworld.net/cgi-local/pvp.cgi?read=2038" TARGET=_self>Re: My Two Cents</A> (Jackal)
</STRONG><FONT SIZE=2 color=#FFFFFF FACE=arial>
<P>> ARRGGGHHH!!!

<BR>&gt; WEREN"T YOU AT THE PVP FIGHT?? 3 HOURS OF FIGHTING!!!
<BR>&gt; Race wars, hell, I didn't blink once during the war, can't wait
<BR>&gt; till the next one!
<BR>&gt; GO PVP!
<P>I played in the DE-Ogre-Human fight the other night, and yes, it was a blast... I have to say that my heart was racing for a good two hours, even though I only actually fought in the melee during the first and second waves of it. After that I ran past into forest of E. commons and kicked the crap out of any dark elves that conned blue to me ;-)... The thing that bugs me about the PvP is that it IS totally unbalanced, unless there is a much swirling melee going on. I have been killed sooooo many times by spellcasters that just root you from afar, then kill you. Even hiding by the inn doesnt work, because the guards evidentaly dont give a shit that one of their own race is being slowly (or not so slowly) blasted. I even had a dark elf root me, hit me about 10 times with some damage causing spell, run up to the guard to regain her mana so nobody could attack her, the finish the job about 5 minutes later. What it UP with that? I think the boys at 989 either need to lower ROOT'S duration to about 10-15 seconds instead of 10-15 minutes, or make the guards react to people that are being hit by damage causing spells near them by going out and killing the spellcaster... I actually think that BOTH need to be done.
</FONT></td></tr></table></P>
